<TITLE> Shibir man nabbed for illegal radio transmission </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, May 31 (bdnews24.com)A member of Islami Chhatra Shibir, the student wing of rightwing opposition Jamaat-e-Islami, was arrested from his college room for illegal radio transmissions, said police in Satkhira on Sunday. Kamrul Islam Sumon, a second-year political science student of at Satkhira Government College, was illegally using FM band frequency, police superintendent Moniruzzaman told bdnews24.com. "The illegal transmission used the FM radio option of a cell-phone to broadcast to many people at a time." "Our wireless system was not working near the college hostel (Alam Hall). Then we suspected there could be a transmitter nearby," said Moniruzzaman. Police also seized two 'Jihadi' books, posters, 21 CDs, a personal computer, an FM radio, a powerful antenna, wires and three clubs made of Goran wood from his room, said sub-inspector Firoz Kabir of Sadar Police Station. Sumon, from Kulia village in Debhata Upazila, Satkhira, was being questioned, Kabir added. Another suspect, Jahidur Rahman of Itagachha, was subsequently arrested based on information given by Sumon during questioning, said police. Both have been detained in a case filed under the Special Powers Act. bdnews24.com/co
